This paper deals with data processing systems and graph construction, which are topics that are commonly studied in computer science. The use of matrices and machine learning clustering techniques also suggests that this paper may fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational geometry (cs.CG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.SI are the most likely as they directly relate to the paper's focus on data processing and graph construction.
